      "content": "To address the internal report discrepancies, the 95% confidence interval reflects the aggregated data set's statistical power, which smooths out localized raw data swings. We are certainly cautious, and the projection incorporates a modeled risk factor for moderate volatility seen in smaller subgroups. I advise framing this as perhaps a \"conservative 90-95% confidence\" depending on the Board's risk appetite, which acknowledges the raw data noise while affirming the overall positive trajectory.",
